
Business Recommendations:

1. Improve Data Quality: Continue to ensure high data quality by regularly handling missing values and outliers.
2. Focus on High-Risk Regions: Implement targeted fraud prevention strategies in regions and categories with higher fraud rates (5%-6%).
3. Leverage Temporal Insights: Monitor transaction peaks during high-risk periods for increased fraud vigilance.
4. Enhance Feature Engineering: Invest in deeper feature engineering to capture more complex fraud patterns and customer behaviors.
5. Adopt Advanced Machine Learning: Utilize specialized algorithms designed for imbalanced datasets to improve fraud detection accuracy.
6. Continuous Model Optimization: Regularly update and tune fraud detection models to adapt to evolving fraud tactics.
